        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The &amp;quot;Nalanda Award&amp;quot; implemented by the Social Justice and Empowerment Department, Gujarat, aims to honor organizations that have significantly contributed to the upliftment of socially and educationally backward communities. This state-level recognition encourages continued efforts in the field of social welfare and highlights best practices that can be replicated across the state.\n",
        "benefits_md": "\n- Financial assistance to the selected organization.\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The \"Nalanda Award\" implemented by the Social Justice and Empowerment Department, Gujarat, recognizes organizations for exceptional work in the field of social welfare, particularly for the socially and educationally disadvantaged sections.",
